	<h1>Maven</h1>
		<section name="Using ESIGate in a Maven project">
			<p>
				Esigate is deployed on Maven	central repository.
			</p>

		</section>


		<section name="Adding dependency on ESIGate">
			<p>
				Then you can add the dependency. For the core API:
			</p>
			<source><![CDATA[
<dependency>
	<groupId>org.esigate</groupId>
	<artifactId>esigate-core</artifactId>
	<version>RELEASE</version>
</dependency>
]]></source>
			<p>
				Note: don't forget to change RELEASE with the latest version.
</p>
			<br />
			<p>
				For the taglib (in master application):
			</p>
			<source><![CDATA[
<dependency>
	<groupId>org.esigate</groupId>
	<artifactId>esigate-taglib</artifactId>
	<version>RELEASE</version>
</dependency>
]]></source>
			<p>
				For the taglib (in a jsf master application):
			</p>
			<source><![CDATA[
<dependency>
	<groupId>org.esigate</groupId>
	<artifactId>esigate-jsf</artifactId>
	<version>RELEASE</version>
</dependency>
]]></source>
			<p>
				For the taglib (in provider application, if java application):
			</p>
			<source><![CDATA[
<dependency>
	<groupId>org.esigate</groupId>
	<artifactId>esigate-taglib-helper</artifactId>
	<version>RELEASE</version>
</dependency>
]]></source>
		</section>
	</body>
